@node Usage
@section Usage
@code{devcontainer} provides multiple commands to interact with
devconntainers. For a full list refer to the documentation of functions
named @code{devcontainer-...}. The important ones are:

@itemize
@item
@code{devcontainer-mode} -- a globally activated minor mode, that you
can just have always activated.
@item
@code{devcontainer-up} -- start the devcontainer of the current project.
@item
@code{devcontainer-restart} -- stop and restart the devcontainer of the
current project.
@item
@code{devcontainer-rebuild-and-restart} -- stop the current project's
devcontainer, delete its docker images and rebuild it. This is useful,
when you for example changed the @code{Dockerfile} of your devcontainer.
@item
@code{devcontainer-execute-command} -- execute an arbitrary command
inside the devcontainer.
@item
@code{devcontainer-term} -- launch a terminal inside the container.
@end itemize

